   <h1>Bryan Martz's Breakfast Scramble</h1>
   <h2> By Bryan Martz <h2>
   <h3>Why Scrambles?</h3>
   
  <p> Breakfast scrambles a versitile dishes that can incorporate a number of different all on one plate. They are easily customizable and can be modified for anyones preferences. However, this recipe is bound to impress anyone. With the perfect mix of flavor, this recipe combines spice and sweetness while providing a savory feel. </p>
  
  <h3>  Preparation </h3>
  <ul>
  <li> Prep time: 10 min </li>
  <li> Cook time: 10 min</li>
  <li> Total time: 20 min </li>
  <li> Yield: 4 servings </li>

  </ul>
  
  <img src= http://www.skinnymom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/AvocadoEggScramble_Ziplist.jpg>
  
  <h3> Ingredients </h3>
  <ol>
  
  <li> 1 teaspoon olive oil</li>
  <li> &frac12; cup red onion</li>
  <li> 1 cup tomato, diced </li>
  <li> 1 jalepeño </li>
  <li> 1 avocado </li>
  <li> 1 cup cooked diced chicken </li>
  <li> 4 whole eggs </li>
  <li> 4 egg whites </li>
  <li> 2 tablespoons water, optional </li>
  <li> 1 tablespoon fresh dill, finely chopped </li>
  <li> Salt and pepper </li>
	  
	  
  </ol>
  <h4> Directions </h4>
  <ol>
  <p> In a non-stick skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the onion, tomatoes, avocados, chicken, and jalepeños for 2 minutes. As it is heating, mixed it once or twice. Once this is done, move to a bowl and let it sit.</p>
  
 <p> In a medium bowl, lightly beat together the whole eggs, egg whites, and water. Pour the egg mixture into the skillet and cook over a medium flame, stirring frequently. Drain any extra water from the tomato mixture and mix gently into the eggs. Toss in the small amount of dill along with the salt and pepper and serve. </p>
 
</ol>
